'''AnyonyƒÅbhƒÅva''', is one of the four [[AbhƒÅva]]s. According to [[Acharya Samant Bhadra]], as related in [[Aptamimansa]], the absence (non-existence) of the present modification of one particular matter [[Matter|substance]] in the present modification of any other matter substance is called ''AnyonyƒÅbhƒÅva'', e.g. the present bitter taste of [[lemon]] is not present in the present sweetness of [[sugar]].<ref>The Four AbhƒÅvas http://www.jainworld.com/education/tatvagyan1/lesson07.htm</ref>

