{{For|the offence in Rugby union|Eye-gouging (rugby union)}} {{too few opinions|date=August 2018}} __NOTOC__ [[Image:eyegouge.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Eye-gouging using the thumb]] '''Eye-gouging''' is the act of pressing or tearing the [[eye]] using the fingers or instruments. Eye-gouging involves a very high risk of [[eye injury]], such as eye loss or blindness.
Eye-gouging as a fighting style was once [[Gouging (fighting style)|a popular form of sport fighting]] in the back-country United States, primarily in the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gorn|first=Elliott J.|date=1985|title="Gouge and Bite, Pull Hair and Scratch": The Social Significance of Fighting in the Southern Backcountry.|jstor=1860747|journal=The American Historical Review|volume=90|issue=1|pages=18‚Äì43|doi=10.2307/1860747}}</ref>
Eye-gouging is prohibited in modern sports. It is a serious offence in rugby football codes where it occurs rarely. It is prohibited in [[combat sports]], but some [[self-defense]] systems teach it.<ref>{{Cite news | issn = 0277-3066 | volume = 22 | issue = 10 | pages = 110 | last = Hosey | first = Timothy |author2=Michael Klaybor | title = Common Sense Self-Defense: For the Woman Who Doesn't Have the Time to Train | work = Black Belt | date = October 1984 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=7toDAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA110&dq=eye%20gouge%20self%20defense&pg=PA110#v=onepage&q&f=false }}</ref> Training in eye-gouging can involve extensive [[grappling]] training to establish control, the eye-gouging itself being practiced with the opponent wearing eye protection such as swimming goggles.<ref>{{Cite news | issn = 0277-3066 | volume = 39 | issue = 10 | pages = 69 | last = Vunak | first = Paul |author2=Erin Vunak | title = Biting and Eye Gouging: Why You Need to Know the Philippine Art of Kino Mutai | work = Black Belt | date = March 2001 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=ns4DAAAAMBAJ&q=eye+gouge+goggles }}</ref> [[Yuki Nakai]] went on to win a bout in the [[Shooto|Vale Tudo Japan 1995]] tournament after his opponent performed an illegal gouge that [[blindness|blinded]] him in his right eye.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.sherdog.com/fighter/Yuki-Nakai-429|title= Nakai talks Vale Tudo, SHOOTO and Rickson |accessdate=2008-11-03 |author= Jason Nowe and Stephen Martinez|date= February 14, 2006 |publisher=sherdog.com}}</ref>
