In [[category theory]], a branch of mathematics, a '''spherical category''' is a [[pivotal category]] (a [[monoidal category]] with [[Trace (mathematics)|trace]]s) in which left and right traces coincide.<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Advances in Mathematics|volume=143|issue=2|pages=357‚Äì375|year=1999|title=Spherical Categories|authors=John W. Barrett, Bruce W. Westbury|accessdate=|doi=10.1006/aima.1998.1800|arxiv=hep-th/9310164}}</ref>
Spherical [[fusion category|fusion categories]] give rise to a family of three-dimensional topological state sum models (a particular formulation of a [[topological quantum field theory]]), the '''Turaev-Viro model''', or rather '''Turaev-Viro-Barrett-Westbury model'''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Turaev-Viro model|url=https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Turaev-Viro+model|website=nLab|accessdate=7 August 2017}}</ref>

